ce:section.ce:para:
Selectivity is another crucial parameter in method validation particularly when employing the GQDs as fluorescence probes due to their susceptibility to interferences from other fluorescent species. Hence, functionalization of the GQDs surface with appropriate moieties is essential to enhance the selectivity towards the target analyte. In the developed method, the functionalization of the GQDs with tetraphenylborate ions provided increased selectivity towards lumateperone. The method was found to be selective, as no significant interference was observed from common excipients present in the formulation such as starch, lactose, and magnesium stearate (Fig. 4
                        ). Additionally, different metals and anions that could potentially quench the fluorescence of the GQDs were also evaluated, and the results showed negligible interferences, confirming the selectivity of the developed method (Fig. 4). Furthermore, standard addition technique was employed to evaluate the matrix effects of the pharmaceutical formulation, and the recoveries obtained were in the range of 99.95–101.68 %, verifying the absence of any significant matrix interferences (Table 2
                        ).
